canonical:
  title: 權侍中影贊
  author: 李詹
  language: lzh
  text: 不詭俗而循禮法不行怪而履平常惟其䂓矩在己是以智圓義方智周乎物而不競義制以事而得宜顯允元老邦家之基苟可以托物而擬倫浩乎萬頃陂溫乎一團春丹靑入神箇是眞身
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 權侍中影贊
  author: 李詹
  language: lzh
  text: 不詭俗而循禮法。不行怪而履平常。惟其䂓矩在己。是以智圓義方。智周乎物而不競。義制以事而得宜。顯允元老。邦家之基。苟可以托物而擬倫。浩乎萬頃陂。溫乎一團春。丹靑入神。箇是眞身。
korean:
  title: 권시중 영찬
  author: 이첨
  language: kor
  text: 세속과 다르게 하는 것 이 예를 따랐으며, 괴상한 일을 행하지 않고 그 상스러운 길을 걸었다. 다만 그의 행동의 척도는 자기 자신에 있으므로 지혜는 모든 것을 잘알면서도 남과 다투지 아니하였고 의리는 모든 일을 처리함에 적당함을 택하였다. 뚜렷하고 미쁘신 원로로서 국가의 기초가 되어 있었다. 만일 자연의 현상 속에서 그와 비슷한 대상을 찾는다면, 넓은 호수의 물이라고 할까. 온화한 그 모습, 한덩어리의 봄이었다. 그림 위에 정신이 들어 간다면 이야말로 정말 그의 몸일 것이다.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0540_010_0340&viewSync=OT
english:
  title: In Praise of Minister Gwon's Portrait
  author: Lee Cham
  language: eng
  text: |-
    He did not deviate from custom, yet upheld the rites and laws;
    He pursued no eccentricities, but walked the ordinary path.
    Yet his measures sprang from within himself alone—
    thus his wisdom became all-encompassing, his righteousness perfectly squared.

    His wisdom flowed through all things without contention,
    his righteousness addressed each matter with fitting grace.
    A venerable elder, luminous and trustworthy,
    the very foundation upon which the realm rests.

    If we search the natural world for his likeness,
    we might call it the waters of a vast lake—
    so temperate in its being, a single mass of spring itself.
    When pigment and brush breathe life upon silk,
    then is captured his truest form.
  footnotes:
    - This work is a praise-inscription (찬, zan) for a portrait of Minister Gwon, likely Gwon Chungchung or another notable historical figure of the early Joseon period. Such portraits were often accompanied by poetic inscriptions celebrating the subject's virtues.
    - 'The imagery of water and spring reflects Confucian ideals of the sage: yielding yet enduring, formless yet substantial, adapting to circumstance while maintaining inner integrity.'
